title: Unemployment rate in Jamaica 2019
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Unemployment rate. In total the number of data points it has is 21.
Overall Unemployment rate has decreased over the Year.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2002 and 2003.
The highest Unemployment rate, of value 15.74 was reached at Year 1999
Minimum Unemployment rate about 9.45 was reached at Year 2018
